</i></p><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-14_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Sport Wales plays a pivotal role in the promotion and development of sports and physical activities across Wales. As a public body sponsored by the Welsh Government, its mission is to encourage more people to participate in sports and to support elite athletes. In this blog, Dr Richard Dune explores the significance of Sport Wales, the key facts and statistics related to its impact, definitions of essential terms, and best practices for implementing relevant legislation and regulations. Ultimately, we will highlight how organisations can achieve compliance with the support of ComplyPlus™ legislation and regulatory compliance management software and training. </span>
</p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-1c11" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-kYHfwS doYKjf pf-16_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hAcGzb cVhebe"><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-17_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-18_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-19_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-21_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Sport Wales was established to foster a culture of active living and to drive participation in sports at all levels. Here are some key facts and statistics:

</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-23_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-24_ pf-text-1">According to the National Survey for Wales, 32% of adults participate in sports three or more times a week.

</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-26_ pf-text-1">Sport Wales supports over 1,500 primary and secondary schools through its various programmes, significantly enhancing youth engagement in physical activities.










 














</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-28_ pf-text-1">The sports sector in Wales contributes approximately £1 billion annually to the Welsh economy and supports around 23,000 jobs.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-30_ pf-text-1">Regular participation in sports reduces the risk of chronic diseases, improves mental health, and enhances overall well-being.











 














</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-32_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-33_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-34_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-36_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-37_ pf-text-1"><strong>Physical activity</strong> - Any bodily movement produced by skeletal muscles that requires energy expenditure. This includes activities such as walking, cycling, sports, and recreational activities.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-39_ pf-text-1"><strong>Compliance </strong>- Adherence to laws, regulations, guidelines, and specifications relevant to an organisation's business processes.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-41_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regulatory bodies</strong> - Organisations that establish and enforce regulations to ensure compliance and protect the public interest. For sports, these include bodies like Sport Wales, the Health and Safety Executive (HSE), and the Care Quality Commission (CQC).










</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-43_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-44_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-45_ pf-heading-1-h3">Best practices for implementation of relevant legislation and regulations
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-47_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Ensuring compliance with legislation and regulations in the sports sector is crucial for safeguarding participants and promoting fair play. Here are some recommended best practices:
</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-49_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-50_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health and safety compliance</strong> - Adhering to the Health and Safety at Work Act 1974 is essential. Sports organisations must conduct risk assessments, provide appropriate training, and ensure safe facilities.










</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-52_ pf-text-1"><strong>Safeguarding </strong>- Protecting children and vulnerable adults is paramount. Organisations should follow guidelines set by the NSPCC and Sport Wales's safeguarding policies, ensuring all staff are trained and vetted.











</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-54_ pf-text-1"><strong>Equality and inclusion</strong> - The Equality Act 2010 mandates non-discrimination in sports. Inclusive practices should be adopted to ensure equal opportunities for all, regardless of age, gender, disability, or ethnicity.












</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-56_ pf-text-1"><strong>Data protection </strong>- Compliance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) is critical. Sports organisations must ensure participants' personal data is handled securely and transparently.














</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-58_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-59_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-60_ pf-heading-1-h3">The impact of sport Wales on local communities
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-62_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Sport Wales's initiatives have a profound impact on local communities. By funding grassroots programmes and community clubs, Sport Wales ensures that sports are accessible to everyone, fostering social cohesion and community spirit.

</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-64_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-65_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-66_ pf-heading-1-h3">Supporting elite athletes
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-68_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">In addition to grassroots development, Sport Wales is crucial in nurturing elite athletes. Through its partnership with the Welsh Institute of Sport, Sport Wales provides high-performance training facilities and support services, enabling athletes to compete on the world stage.


</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-70_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-71_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-72_ pf-heading-1-h3">Promoting health and wellbeing
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-74_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Regular physical activity is linked to numerous health benefits, including reduced risk of cardiovascular diseases, improved mental health, and enhanced quality of life. Sport Wales's programmes encourage healthy lifestyles, reducing healthcare services' burden.



</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-76_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-77_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-78_ pf-heading-1-h3">Compliance and governance in sports organisations
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-80_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Sports organisations must navigate a complex landscape of regulations and guidelines. Effective governance and compliance strategies are essential to ensure that these organisations operate within legal frameworks and maintain the highest standards of safety and integrity.




</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-82_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-83_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-84_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-86_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-87_ pf-text-1"><strong>Implement comprehensive training</strong> - Regular training for staff and volunteers on health and safety, safeguarding, and equality issues is crucial. ComplyPlus™ offers extensive training modules tailored to the needs of sports organisations.










</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-89_ pf-text-1"><strong>Utilise compliance management software </strong>- Technology such as ComplyPlus™ can streamline compliance processes, ensuring that organisations stay updated with the latest regulations and standards.












</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-91_ pf-text-1"><strong>Engage with regulatory bodies</strong> - Regular communication with Sport Wales and other regulatory bodies ensures that organisations are aware of any changes in legislation and can adapt their practices accordingly.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-93_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-94_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-95_ pf-heading-1-h3">Conclusion
